    public class BigdataSparqlTest
extends SPARQLQueryTest
    Test harness for running the SPARQL test suites. This version runs against a Journal without full read/write transaction support.
    Author:
    Bryan Thompson

    • Field Detail

      • cannotInlineTests

        protected static final Collection<String> cannotInlineTests
        We cannot use inlining for these test because we do normalization on numeric values and these tests test for syntactic differences, i.e. 01 != 1.

      • badTests

        public static final Collection<String> badTests
        The tests test things that are no longer in the spec or that use an illegal syntax.

      • knownBadTests

        public static final Collection<String> knownBadTests
        These tests fail but should not. They are conditionally disabled based on BigdataStatics.runKnownBadTests. This is done as a convenience to 'green' up CI.

      • unicodeStrengthIdentical

        protected static final Collection<String> unicodeStrengthIdentical
        The following tests require Unicode configuration for identical comparisons. This appears to work with {ASCII,IDENTICAL} or {JDK,IDENTICAL} but not with {ICU,IDENTICAL} for some reason.

      • testURIs

        protected static final Collection<String> testURIs
        An array of URIs for tests to be run. When null or empty the default test suite is run. When specified, only the tests matching these test URIs are run.

      • getQueryConnection

        protected BigdataSailRepositoryConnection getQueryConnection(org.openrdf.repository.Repository dataRep)
                                                      throws Exception
        Overridden to use BigdataSail.getReadOnlyConnection() as a workaround to the test harness which invokes BigdataSail.getConnection() multiple times from within the same thread. When full transactions are not enabled, that will delegate to BigdataSail.getUnisolatedConnection(). Only one unisolated connection is permitted at a time. While different threads will block to await the unisolated connection, that method will throw an exception if there is an attempt by a single thread to obtain more than one instance of the unisolated connection (since that operation would otherwise deadlock).
        Throws:
        Exception
